  <section class="pcm-how pcm-section" aria-label="How the Calm Mat works">
    <div style="max-width:1000px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="pcm-section-title">How it works</h2>
      <div class="pcm-steps">
        <div class="pcm-step pcm-reveal">
          <span class="pcm-step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="pcm-step-title">Load and position</h3>
            <p class="pcm-step-desc">Spread a thin layer of your dog&rsquo;s favourite paste across all four texture zones. Place the mat in the designated departure spot &mdash; the same location, every session. Consistency builds the conditioned cue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcm-step pcm-reveal">
          <span class="pcm-step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="pcm-step-title">Depart without ceremony</h3>
            <p class="pcm-step-desc">No drawn-out goodbyes. No reassurance. Leave while your dog is engaged. The slow licking activates the parasympathetic nervous system before cortisol has time to spike during that critical 30&ndash;40 minute window.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcm-step pcm-reveal">
          <span class="pcm-step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="pcm-step-title">Extend the window</h3>
            <p class="pcm-step-desc">Following the protocol, session length increases incrementally over 30 days. The mat becomes an environmental anchor &mdash; a reliable signal that calm is the expected state. The anxiety retreats as the behaviour solidifies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

