    <div class="pcm-faq-inner">
      <h2 class="pcm-section-title">Common questions</h2>
      <div class="pcm-faq-list">

        <div class="pcm-faq-item">
          <button class="pcm-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" type="button">
            <span>Does the mat work on its own?</span>
            <svg class="pcm-faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 6l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="pcm-faq-a" hidden>
            <p>No. The mat is a tool, not a treatment. It creates a reliable physiological anchor &mdash; slow licking during the cortisol window &mdash; but systematic desensitisation is what resolves separation anxiety. Without a protocol, the mat provides enrichment. Within one, it accelerates progress.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pcm-faq-item">
          <button class="pcm-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" type="button">
            <span>Which colour pair should I choose?</span>
            <svg class="pcm-faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 6l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="pcm-faq-a" hidden>
            <p>The Protocol Pair (Milk White + Sky Blue) is the standard setup used across all four protocol phases. The Regulation Pair suits highly reactive or sensitive dogs in foundation work &mdash; softer tones reduce visual stimulation. The Anchor Pair is designed for Phase 3 threshold management, where visual contrast sharpens the conditioned cue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pcm-faq-item">
          <button class="pcm-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" type="button">
            <span>Is it safe for all dogs?</span>
            <svg class="pcm-faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 6l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="pcm-faq-a" hidden>
            <p>Yes. Food-grade silicone, BPA-free confirmed. The 99 suction cups keep the mat fixed during sessions &mdash; this matters for maintaining the environmental cue. Supervise the first few sessions to confirm your dog engages correctly rather than chewing the mat.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pcm-faq-item">
          <button class="pcm-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" type="button">
            <span>What if my dog isn&rsquo;t interested in the mat?</span>
            <svg class="pcm-faq-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 6l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="pcm-faq-a" hidden>
            <p>Common in the first 1&ndash;2 sessions. Use a high-value paste &mdash; peanut butter, soft cheese, meat paste &mdash; spread into all four texture zones. Freezing the mat overnight extends engagement time significantly. Most dogs are reliably engaged within 3 sessions once the conditioned cue begins to form.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pcm-faq-item">
